NDFSK Assails U.S. Adventurous War Moves 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of south Korea (NDFSK) issued a statement denouncing the U.S. for its adventurous war moves on December 3, according to Internet site Kuguk Jonson.
 Referring to the fact that the U.S. has mapped out reckless war scenarios against the north at different phases and pushed ahead with the war moves to put the scenarios into practice in a premeditated manner over the last scores of years, the statement goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These operational plans include "OPLAN 5030," "OPLAN 5027," and "OPLAN 5029", a chain of the phased-out anti-north war scenarios. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those anti-north war scenarios clearly indicate the persistent and vicious nature of the U.S. arrogant moves to stifle the north by force and swallow up the whole of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is clearly evidenced by the fact that the U.S. has massively deployed new type ultra-modern war equipment in and around the Korean Peninsula and ceaselessly staged "RSOI," "Foal Eagle" and "Ulji Focus Lens-04" drills and other large-scale anti-north war exercises in the air and sea and on the land, driving the situation on the peninsula to the brink of a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. truly wants peace and a peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue on the peninsula it should immediately withdraw its hostile policy towards the DPRK and scrap all the dangerous anti-DPRK war scenarios. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people from all walks of life should turn out as one in the anti-U.S., anti-war struggle to prevent the disaster of war and safeguard peace and security through the national cooperation in order to cope with the serious situation on the peninsula which is inching close to the brink of a war hour by hour due to the U.S.

KPA under Supreme Commandership of Kim Jong Il Praised in Czech Republic 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks took place in Mlada Boleslav, the Czech Republic, on the occasion of the 13th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army (KPA).
 Jiri Jarka, chairman of the Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association, said at the talks that the KPA, heir to the glorious traditions of the anti-Japanese armed struggle waged by President Kim Il Sung, has grown to be invincible forces which even the U.S. styling itself the only superpower in the world dares not provoke, and to be a main force of the revolution successfully undertaking not only the duty to defend the country but any difficult tasks for socialist construction thanks to the Songun policy pursued by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that socialism would steadily advance in the DPRK, undeterred, as long as it is defended by the KPA under the supreme commandership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Member of the Chamber of Deputies in the Parliament Stanislav Grolspic noted he was deeply impressed by the fact that the Korean people have made great successes in socialist construction, united close around Kim Jong Il despite the evermore pronounced U.S. hostile policy toward their country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia will extend support and solidarity to the Korean people in their struggle for national reunification and do a lot in the Parliament, too, to be helpful to the development of the relations with the DPRK and positively cooperative with it, he noted.

Meeting of General Onward March for Songun Revolution to Be Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- A meeting of the general onward march for the Songun revolution will be held in Pyongyang early in February next year, 10 years after the Workers' Party of Korea started pursuing the great Songun policy.
 The meeting will review the successes and experience gained in the last decade and discuss the tasks for more dynamically accelerating the grand march to accomplish the WPK's Juche-oriented Songun revolutionary cause and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It will be attended by servicepersons, officials and working people who have performed heroic feats in defending the country and building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation while resolutely smashing the imperialists' vicious moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK through the drive to devotedly implement the Party's Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will be a historic meeting as it will mark a new milestone in conveying the WPK's glorious history of the Songun revolution and its Songun leadership exploits to posterity and encouraging the whole party, all the servicepersons and people to turn out in the general onward march for the Songun revolution on the occasion of the 60th anniversaries of the WPK and the country's liberation.

Settlement of Issue of "Comfort Women" for Imperial Japanese Army Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- Various organizations in south Korea made public working plans for 2005 for finding a settlement of the issue of the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army. They envisage "a million-signature campaign for international solidarity," meetings and information service.
 Members of the Council for the Solution of the Issue of the Volunteers Corps on Dec. 1 called a press conference at the education hall of the council for the above-said purpose and made public those working plans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the press conference referred to the fact that diverse movements for the settlement of the issue are now under way worldwide. They called for more vigorously conducting solidarity actions demanding Japan's formal apology to the victims and so on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The press conference was attended by representatives of an international women's organization and women's organizations of seven countries for the settlement of the issue of "comfort women" for the Japanese army including the Philippines, the Netherlands and Indonesia.

South Korean Students Urged to Take Lead in Fight for Abolition of NSL 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- Members of the Central Standing Committee of the South Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) made public an appeal on December 3, calling upon the youth and students to take the lead in the fight for the repeal of the "National Security Law" by their uninterrupted practical action.
 Members of the organization have been on a hunger strike for over 30 days in demand of the total repeal of the NSL, the appeal said, adding: The anti-reunification forces headed by the Grand National Party are kicking and struggling to keep the evil law and the Uri Party is behaving against the will of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Victory is certain as long as there is the strength of the people aspiring after reunification and there are our students who have always fought in the van of the struggle for the demands of the times and the nation, the appeal stated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Seoul District Federation of University Student Councils under Hanchongryon on December 1 issued a statement titled "Let's put an end to the disgraceful history of 56 years and proudly greet a new society and the era of independent reunification". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For 56 years since its enactment the NSL has been applied to suppressing human rights, holding down the freedom of thought and crudely trampling on the desire of the 70 million fellow countrymen for reunification, said the statement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Never before has the people's fervor for the abolition of the NSL surged into such a high tide as today, noted the statement, calling upon all the students to turn out in the fight for the repeal of the NSL.

Japan's Moves Harassing Peace and Stability in Northeast Asia under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- Japan in a new defence program termed the DPRK, China and Russia untransparent and unstable elements in the way of ensuring regional security. Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun Tuesday brands Japan as a dangerous force of aggression harassing peace and stability in Northeast Asia.
 The designation of the DPRK and countries around it as unstable and untransparent elements by the Japanese reactionaries discloses more glaringly the despicable true colors of those who are accustomed to pulling up others to attain their militarist purpose, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By misleading public opinion by the above-said allegation, the Japanese military authorities seek to justify their scheme to convert the country into a military giant and get into full stride in promoting it and thereby hold the hegemonic position in Northeast Asia. They also seek to pressurize and contain their neighboring countries and realize their ambition for military expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While equipping the SDF with modern, large-size and long-range weapons, the Japanese reactionaries are working round the clock to secure a legal foundation whereby to launch into an overseas aggression through the total mobilization of material and manpower potentials of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their maneuvers to include an article allowing Japan to take part in armed actions in the constitution to be revised prompt us to guess to what a stage they have gone in their moves for overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And they are putting fresh muscles into the "Japan-U.S. security alliance" under the pretext of coping with threat in Northeast Asia. What they seek in this is to realize with the U.S. backing their design for the "Greater East Asia Co-prosperity Sphere" which they failed to realize in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese militarists' reckless moves for military expansion under the pretext of "coping with threat" are escalating instability in Northeast Asia and increasing the danger of war there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should bear in mind that their frantic acts for military expansion overseas is a suicidal act that will hasten their own destruction.

Japan's Moves to Emerge Military Giant under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- The director general of the Japan Defence�@Agency during his recent U.S. junket expressed its intention to put the�@missile defense system (MD) now in the process of Japan-U.S. joint�@technological research on a production line.
 Almost timed to coincide with this, the Mitsubishi Heavy Industry Company�@of Japan and the Lockeed Martin Company of the U.S. concluded a patent�@contract on producing PAC- 3, main component of the MD. Under this contract�@Japan will start a serial production of PAC-3 next year and this type of�@missiles will be deployed in Japan in real earnest from the fiscal 2008. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In another development, Japan additionally dispatched 200 servicemen of its�@Ground "Self-Defense Force" to Iraq under the mask of "volunteers for Iraqi�@reconstruction." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on the recent military moves of Japan, Minju Joson Tuesday says�@this is a grave development as it means an important step forward in its bid�@to emerge a military giant and part of the moves to realize its militarist�@ambition for overseas invasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan paints the MD as mere means to protect the security of the country�@from someone's "missile threat." But its real purpose is to have in place as�@early as possible military means to invade other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's dispatch of its GSDF to Iraq despite risk is not a separate issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It takes the U.S. military presence in Iraq as the best opportunity for�@massively dispatching the SDF overseas in a bid to have its right to�@military operation overseas recognized internationally and make it practice�@to conduct such operations in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This should be censured as an act of dampening humankind's desire for peace�@and deserves the world peace-loving people's curse and condemnation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are well advised not to rashly act, pondering�@over the catastrophic consequences to be entailed by their militarist moves�@for overseas aggression.

Sinister Actions of U.S. and IAEA Accused
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Korean National Peace�@Committee issued a statement on Dec. 6 denouncing the United States for�@escalating its stand-off with the DPRK over its "nuclear issue" and the�@International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) for acting its servant in a bid to�@cover up the dangerous nuclear issue of south Korea.
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The IAEA made such unfair decision to hush up south Korea's issue of secret�@nuclear experiments the way it thinks fit entirely under the U.S. backstage�@wirepulling and pressure and due to the south Korean authorities lobbying�@operation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to achieve peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula, it is�@necessary to probe the truth about south Korea's nuclear development and not�@to tolerate the U.S. self-righteous double standards and arbitrary practices�@under any circumstances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Without doing this it is not possible to expect the denuclearization of the�@Korean Peninsula and any improvement in the inter-Korean relations nor is it�@possible to ensure peace in Asia and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and the IAEA should stop such arrogant actions as applying double�@standards as regards the nuclear issue and acting international judges. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement expressed the belief that the south Korean people of all�@strata would clearly see through the danger of the nuclear experiments�@conducted by the south Korean authorities under the U.S. protection and turn�@out in a dynamic struggle to frustrate the reckless moves of the U.S. and�@its allies for a nuclear war to bring its disaster to the peninsula.

U.S. Denounced for Increasing War Danger
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- The deployment of new-type Patriot missiles�@by the United States in Kwangju, south Korea, has been completed and this�@indicates that its scheme to start a new war on the Korean Peninsula is�@being stepped up in the last stage, notes a Minju Joson analyst today.
 He continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. outcries for "dialogue" and "peace" are no more than a ruse to�@cover up the preparations for a war against the DPRK. It is shipping�@ultra-modern military hardware into south Korea behind the curtain of�@"dialogue" and "peace" so as to mount a preemptive attack on the DPRK by�@surprise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. was adamant enough to deploy the new-type Patriot missiles in�@Kwangju, turning a deaf ear to the strong opposition of the south Korean�@people. This is a downright mockery of and insult to the latter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The robber-like colors of the U.�r. which does not bother to pay heed to�@the south Korean people when it comes to its aggressive aim, came into a�@glaring light this time again. The Korean nation in the north and the south�@can never escape from the danger of a nuclear war without frustrating the�@U.S. war moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no change in the stand of the DPRK for answering good-will with�@good-will and toughness with super toughness. The DPRK will continue to�@increase its war deterrent force in the future, too, as the U.S. is getting�@overheated in war preparations against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be well advised to cool its head buoyed by fervor for�@aggression on the DPRK and withdraw its forces from south Korea, clearly�@seeing who is its adversary.

Folk Food Culture Encouraged in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- The folk food culture has been encouraged�@in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 A Korean food competition and national local special food exhibition were�@held in June and September respectively. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dishes presented to the competition by the Okryu and Chongryu�@restaurants and other catering establishments demonstrated fine aspects of�@Korean food unique in taste, aroma, shape and color. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibition was participated in by more than 50 units including�@provincial societies under the Korean Food Society, and public service and�@external service establishments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display there were over 700 kinds of local special dishes including�@River Taedong gray mullet soup, Pyongyang white kimchi, hare meat quenelle,�@chicken and carp soup, hot myongthae soup, mixed dish of boletus and beef,�@and cake made of frozen potatoes. Also displayed were 260-odd folk holiday�@dishes including boiled rice mixed with four other grains, noodle with meat�@in flat vessel, cake made with wheat-flour, oil and honey, loach soup,�@soybean malt paste and peppered bean paste. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those in the public catering field had toured different areas of the�@country to find out properties and cooking method of traditional food and�@improve their cooking method. The traditional food and drinks exhibited by�@them caught the eyes of visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Colorful functions including contests of radishes pickled in salt water and�@local special food shows were also organized to widely introduce the folk�@dishes into dietary life of people and service in North Hwanghae, Kangwon�@and other provinces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, national food restaurants have made their appearance in each�@district of Pyongyang and local areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il has paid deep attention to the work of carrying forward�@the heritage of the folk food.

Quality Injection-molded Shoes Produced in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- The Ryuwon Footwear Factory in the�@Democratic People's Republic of Korea is mass-producing quality�@injection-molded shoes.
 The shoes with two-color sole are smart, soft and flexible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Particularly children's shoes are in great demand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The factory has made technical inventions including a two-color-sole mould�@to meet the growing demand for the shoes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The factory is now producing various models of quality injection-molded�@shoes with multi-color soles and leather. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among its products are boots, sandals, leather shoes and mountain-climbing�@boots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are popular in local and foreign markets.

Historic Relics Discovered in Kaesong Area
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- Historic relics and remains have been�@unearthed in twelve spots of the first stage construction site of the�@Kaesong industrial zone, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Among them are rude stone implements in the Paleolithic Age, earthenware�@fragments in the Neolithic Age and iron scissors, porcelains and broken�@roof-tiles in the periods of Koryo (918-1392) and Ri Dynasty (1392-1910). 
 Forty historic relics were also excavated. They include a ruined house in�@the early period of the Middle Ages and four ruined buildings, 19 cellar�@tombs, 11 limestone tombs, two cremation tombs and one stone tomb belonging�@to the period of Koryo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dr. Ri Chang On of the Archaeological Institute of the Academy of Social�@Science told the KCNA: The relics and remains prove that the Korean�@ancestors had created and developed their own culture from the dawn of the�@human history. They provide more materials for the study of the cultural�@heritage of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The survey, collection and excavation of the relics were conducted jointly�@by scientists of the north and south from late April to late July.

U.S. Urged to Cancel Scenarios for War against DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the�@Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland issued a statement Monday in which�@he urged the United States to drop its hostile policy toward the DPRK and�@cancel all its dangerous scenarios for a war against the DPRK if it truly�@wants peace on the Korean Peninsula and a peaceful solution to its nuclear�@issue.
 The statement referred to the fact that the U.S. has secretly worked out�@and actively pursued very dangerous war scenarios to attack the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These facts clearly prove that the U.S. worked out three dimensional war�@plans involving not only the period of emergency but the pre- and post-war�@periods in the conception of war long ago and has steadily modified and�@supplemented them in a bid to stifle the DPRK by force, the statement said,�@and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is working despicably to stifle the DPRK by force behind the scene�@of dialogue despite its lip-service to the peaceful solution to the nuclear�@issue on the Korean Peninsula and the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation on the Korean Peninsula is, in fact, little different from�@that in the war time as the U.S. scenario for a war of aggression is�@becoming a reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Peace has so far been preserved on the peninsula and the security of the�@nation defended entirely thanks to the patriotic policy, the peace-loving�@great Songun policy pursued by the DPRK for the country and the nation, and�@its strong deterrent force which no formidable enemy can ever match. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called upon the south Koreans and the world progressive�@people to turn out in the anti-U.S. struggle to avert a war and defend peace�@to cope with the situation on the Korean Peninsula which is getting tenser�@than ever before due to the U.S.
